  "response": "Here's a breakdown of how Amazon supports small businesses:\n\n1. Amazon Marketplace\n- Sell products directly online\n- Access to large customer base\n- Multiple selling plans (Individual/Professional)\n- Global selling opportunities\n\n2. Fulfillment by Amazon (FBA)\n- Store products in Amazon warehouses\n- Amazon handles shipping and customer service\n- Prime shipping eligibility\n- Reduces logistics complexity\n\n3. Amazon Business\n- B2B marketplace for business supplies\n- Volume discounts\n- Tax-exempt purchasing\n- Business-specific pricing\n\n4. Funding & Support\n- Amazon Lending program\n- Small business loans\n- Seller training resources\n- Marketing support tools\n\n5. Additional Services\n- Brand Registry\n- Advertising platforms\n- Analytics and performance tracking\n- Product visibility tools\n\n6. Low-Cost Entry\n- Minimal upfront investment\n- Pay-per-sale model\n- Easy setup process\n- No mandatory monthly fees (Individual plan)\n\n7. Specialized Programs\n- Handmade at Amazon\n- Amazon Launchpad\n- Support for artisan/startup businesses\n\nChallenges:\n- Competitive marketplace\n- Potential fee structures\n- Platform dependency\n- Competition from other sellers\n\nOverall, Amazon provides comprehensive tools to help small businesses scale and reach broader markets.",
